# The following examples are for using the VAULT command space
# to read and write to the TEA DATABASE (a persistent kind of vault storage)
# NOTE: these functions should work as is for both WEB and CLI TEA

# store value "this is a menu" under key "MENU" in the DB
v@:MENU:{this is a menu}

# check (even in a different program or after quiting)
# how long a value in DB record "MENU" is
v!@:MENU # should return "14"

# store value in AI as some value in DB
z.: # fetches current environment-platform params
v@:MYPLATFORM # stores them in TDB under name "MYPLATFORM"
